SIMPLE: lickerish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lickerish
<hw>Lick"er*ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Lecherous</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Eager; craving; urged by desire; eager to taste or
enjoy; greedy.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>lickerish</xex> palate of the
glutton.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tempting the appetite; dainty.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Lickerish</xex> baits, fit to insnare a brute.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Lecherous; lustful.</def> <rj><au>Robert of
Brunne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Lick"er*ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Lick"er*ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lickerous</ent>⟦br⟧
